<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Revenge1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Revenge,</orth> subst. return of an injury, retaliation, vengeance: <bibl n="shak. luc 1823" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1823</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.99" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 99</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.2.222" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 222</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.281" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 281</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.281" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 281</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 56</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 56</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 56</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 1, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.374" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 374</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.124" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 2, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.31" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 2, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.190" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 1, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.271" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 271</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 157</bibl> etc. <emph>in r.</emph> == by way of retaliation: <bibl n="shak. luc 236" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 236</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 236" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 236</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.2.110" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 2, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.133" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 2, 11</bibl>; cf. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.5.35" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 5, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.127" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 127</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.3.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 3, 41</bibl>. <emph>his r.</emph> sometimes == the act of revenging him: Lucr. Arg. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.3.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 3, 41</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.5.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 5, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.127" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 127</bibl>. cf. <cit><quote>my death's r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.6.39" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 6, 39</bibl></cit>. With <emph>for</emph>: <cit><quote>prophesied r. for it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.186" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 186</bibl></cit>. With <cit><quote>on:</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1180" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1180</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. son 149.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 149, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.172" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 172</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.265" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 265</bibl>. H8 <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">1, 2</bibl>, <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">1, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 1.137" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.117" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.4.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 4, 37</bibl>. Plur. <emph>--s,</emph> in the same sense: <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.140" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 140</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.385" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 385</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.456" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 456</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.5.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 5, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.2.44" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.85" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.4.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 4, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.4.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 4, 32</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mac 5.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 2, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.7.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 7, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.5.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 5, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.159" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 159</bibl>. <emph>to have one's r.</emph> or <cit><quote>--s:</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.282" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 282</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.5.1" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 1</bibl>. <cit><quote>to render vengeance and r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.67" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 67</bibl></cit> (cf. <emph>Render</emph>). <emph>to take r.</emph> or <cit><quote>--s:</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 4, 33</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.117" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.4.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 4, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.7.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 7, 7</bibl>.
